// REV-08 / D-26 — banned-word lint on RENDERED formatter output.
//
// Defence-in-depth Layer 2 of the ADR-0005 §Enforcement strategy:
//
//   Layer 1 (source-level):   scripts/ci-grep-gates.sh Gate A scans every
//                              .ts / .md file for the 10 banned tokens.
//   Layer 2 (rendered-level): THIS file runs every formatter on every
//                              relevant fixture and re-checks the
//                              RENDERED output for banned tokens + emoji.
//
// Why both: source-grep catches static strings but cannot see content
// generated by string concatenation (a catalog entry interpolated into a
// template). Layer 2 closes that gap by exercising the full pipeline
// fixture → service → formatter → string and lint-checking the output.
//
// The contract test also runs the lint against the three catalog
// modules (ACTION_CATALOG, DECISION_PROMPT_CATALOG, API_GAP_ENTRIES) at
// module load — same as the per-module sibling tests in Plan 04-05 /
// 04-06, but consolidated here so a single failing assertion identifies
// the offending catalog entry by id.
//
// Plan 04-10 will extend this test with the 4 prompt-instruction
// constants once they land (PROMPT_INSTRUCTIONS at the MCP prompt
// surface). Until then the prompt subset is intentionally empty.
//
// Pure (no I/O outside readFileSync + the in-memory DB helpers used by
// the daily/weekly arms). No console.*, no process.stdout.write.

